Los Angeles in March became the first U.S. city to hit an average gas price of $6 per gallon. Last Wednesday, the average cost for a gallon of regular gas reached $6.08 in the city, setting a new record. The average cost of living continues to hit levels unseen in 40 years. CGTN Stringer in Los Angeles visited gas stations and supermarkets to see the current prices of everyday consumer goods for average Americans and how it has affected their life.